  <summary date="2022-04-18T19:28:38Z" status="Introduced in House">Recognizing the Unborn Act of 2021

This bill replaces the term fetus with unborn child throughout federal law, including provisions relating to abortions and medical research. The bill also creates a default statutory definition for unborn child: a child in utero, or a member of the species Homo sapiens, at any stage of development, who is carried in the womb.</summary>
